✅ 2. Use Proper HTTP Methods

Each HTTP method has a meaning:

| Method    | Purpose    |
| --------- | ---------- |
| GET       | Fetch data |
| POST      | Create     |
| PUT/PATCH | Update     |
| DELETE    | Remove     |


Example:

POST /users

→ Creates a user

GET /users/5

→ Fetch user with ID 5

